{% liquid
  assign heading = section.settings.heading
%}

<div class="section spacing-style color-{{ section.settings.color_scheme }}">
  <div class="section-inner page-width">
    <div class="care-content">
      {% if heading != blank %}
        <h1 class="heading-1">{{ heading }}</h1>
      {% endif %}

      <p class="care-intro">Proper care ensures your JACKEETA pieces remain beautiful for years to come. Follow these guidelines to maintain the quality and longevity of your garments.</p>

      <div class="care-sections">
        <div class="care-category">
          <h2>GENERAL CARE</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Always check the care label inside your garment before washing</li>
            <li>Separate light and dark colors</li>
            <li>Turn garments inside out before washing to preserve color and texture</li>
            <li>Use cold water when possible to prevent shrinkage and color fading</li>
            <li>Avoid overloading the washing machine</li>
            <li>Remove items from the washer promptly to prevent wrinkles</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="care-by-fabric">
          <h2>CARE BY FABRIC</h2>
          
          <div class="fabric-item">
            <h3>COTTON</h3>
            <p>Machine wash cold with like colors. Tumble dry low or hang to dry. Iron on medium heat if needed. Cotton may shrink slightly after the first wash.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="fabric-item">
            <h3>WOOL</h3>
            <p>Hand wash in cold water with wool-specific detergent or dry clean. Lay flat to dry away from direct heat. Never wring or twist. Store folded, not hung, to maintain shape.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="fabric-item">
            <h3>SILK</h3>
            <p>Dry clean recommended. If hand washing, use cold water and silk detergent. Never twist or wring. Roll in a towel to remove excess water, then lay flat to dry. Iron on low heat while slightly damp.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="fabric-item">
            <h3>LINEN</h3>
            <p>Machine wash cold on gentle cycle. Tumble dry low or hang to dry. Iron while slightly damp on high heat. Linen naturally wrinkles – this is part of its charm.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="fabric-item">
            <h3>DENIM</h3>
            <p>Wash inside out in cold water. Hang to dry to prevent shrinkage and preserve color. Iron on high heat if needed. Limit washing to every 5-6 wears to extend life.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="fabric-item">
            <h3>CASHMERE</h3>
            <p>Hand wash in cool water with cashmere shampoo. Gently squeeze – never wring. Roll in towel to remove moisture, then lay flat to dry. Store folded with cedar or lavender sachets.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="fabric-item">
            <h3>LEATHER</h3>
            <p>Professional leather cleaning only. Spot clean with a damp cloth. Store in breathable garment bag. Apply leather conditioner twice a year. Keep away from direct heat and sunlight.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="care-category">
          <h2>STAIN REMOVAL</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Oil-based stains:</strong> Apply dish soap before washing</li>
            <li><strong>Wine/Coffee:</strong> Blot immediately with cold water, then wash</li>
            <li><strong>Ink:</strong> Dab with rubbing alcohol using a cotton ball</li>
            <li><strong>Makeup:</strong> Pre-treat with liquid laundry detergent</li>
            <li>Always test stain removers on an inconspicuous area first</li>
            <li>Never put stained items in the dryer – heat sets stains</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="care-category">
          <h2>STORAGE TIPS</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Store in a cool, dry place away from direct sunlight</li>
            <li>Use padded hangers for structured pieces like blazers and coats</li>
            <li>Fold heavy knits to prevent stretching</li>
            <li>Use garment bags for special occasion pieces</li>
            <li>Allow pieces to air out before storing</li>
            <li>Use cedar blocks or lavender sachets to deter moths</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="care-symbols">
          <h2>CARE SYMBOLS GUIDE</h2>
          <div class="symbols-grid">
            <div class="symbol-item">
              <div class="symbol-icon">△</div>
              <p>Do Not Bleach</p>
            </div>
            <div class="symbol-item">
              <div class="symbol-icon">○</div>
              <p>Dry Clean Only</p>
            </div>
            <div class="symbol-item">
              <div class="symbol-icon">□</div>
              <p>Tumble Dry Low</p>
            </div>
            <div class="symbol-item">
              <div class="symbol-icon">⊓</div>
              <p>Iron Low Heat</p>
            </div>
            <div class="symbol-item">
              <div class="symbol-icon">◡</div>
              <p>Hand Wash Only</p>
            </div>
            <div class="symbol-item">
              <div class="symbol-icon">⌒</div>
              <p>Do Not Wring</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{% stylesheet %}
  .care-content {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .heading-1 {
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .care-intro {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .care-sections {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 64px;
  }

  .care-category h2,
  .care-by-fabric h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .care-category ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .care-category li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
    padding-left: 24px;
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .care-category li::before {
    content: '•';
    position: absolute;
    left: 8px;
  }

  .care-by-fabric {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 32px;
  }

  .fabric-item {
    padding: 24px;
    background: #f8f8f8;
    border-left: 3px solid #000;
  }

  .fabric-item h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .fabric-item p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
  }

  .care-symbols {
    padding: 48px;
    background: #f8f8f8;
  }

  .symbols-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr));
    gap: 32px;
  }

  .symbol-item {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .symbol-icon {
    font-size: 48px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .symbol-item p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 749px) {
    .care-sections {
      gap: 48px;
    }

    .symbols-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 24px;
    }

    .care-symbols {
      padding: 32px 24px;
    }
  }
{% endstylesheet %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Care Instructions",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "Heading",
      "default": "Care Instructions"
    },
    {
      "type": "color_scheme",
      "id": "color_scheme",
      "label": "Color scheme",
      "default": "scheme-1"
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Care Instructions"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
